# PR-Based Delivery Workflow

Whenever the user asks me to complete a step/task and I finish it, I MUST deliver
it as a Pull Request rather than committing directly to `main`.

## Required steps after finishing a task

1. Create (or switch to) a dedicated feature branch, e.g. `feat/<short-name>` or
   `fix/<short-name>`. Never commit the work directly on `main`.
2. Commit the changes with a clear, conventional message (e.g. `feat: ...`,
   `fix: ...`, `chore: ...`).
3. Push the branch: `git push -u origin <branch>`.
4. Open a PR with `gh pr create`, providing a `## Summary` and `## Test plan`.
5. Return the PR URL to the user.

## Notes

- One PR per completed step the user requests.
- Keep `main` clean; all work lands through PRs.
- If pushing to GitHub fails with a network error (e.g. `Connection was reset`),
  report it and offer proxy/SSH remedies instead of silently giving up.
